f\u5b97\u53bf}}\n|Gu\u01cengz\u014dng Xi\u00e0n\n|270,000\n|493\n|548\n|-\n|[[Pingxiang County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u5e73\u4e61\u53bf}}\n|P\u00edngxi\u0101ng Xi\u00e0n\n|280,000\n|406\n|670\n|-\n|[[Wei County, Xingtai|Wei County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u5a01\u53bf}}\n|W\u0113i Xi\u00e0n\n|540,000\n|994\n|543\n|-\n|[[Qinghe County, Hebei|Qinghe County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u6e05\u6cb3\u53bf}}\n|Q\u012bngh\u00e9 Xi\u00e0n\n|360,000\n|501\n|719\n|-\n|[[Linxi County, Hebei|Linxi County]]\n|{{lang|zh-hans|\u4e34\u897f\u53bf}}\n|L\u00ednx\u012b Xi\u00e0n\n|330,000\n|542\n|609\n|}\n\n==Economy==\nXingtai is the most important base for natural resources in North China, producing 20 million metric tonnes of coal annually. It also features the largest power plant in the southern part of this region of China, with an output of 2.06 [[Gigawatt|GW]].<ref name = \"Gov't Intro\">{{cite web\n| url = http://info.xingtai.gov.cn/content.jsp?code=000721000/2008-00043\n| script-title=zh:\u90a2\u53f0\u5e02\u60c5\u4ecb\u7ecd\n| publisher = Xingtai People's Government\n| language = zh-hans\n| accessdate = 2011-05-20}}</ref>\n\n==Transport==\nLocated on the [[Jingguang Railway|Beijing\u2212Guangzhou]] and the [[Jingjiu Railway|Beijing\u2212Kowloon]] Railways, as well as the [[Jingshen Expressway|Beijing\u2212Shenzhen]], [[Qingyin Expressway|Qingdao\u2212Yinchuan]] (, and [[Xinglin Expressway|Xingtai\u2212Linqing]] Expressways, Xingtai is a transport hub connecting the [[East China|Eastern]], Northern, and [[Central China]].\n\n==Notable persons==\n* [[Ren Xuefeng]]\n* [[Pangzai]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Beiguozhuang]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Xingtai}}\n* [http://www.xingtai.gov.cn/ Xingtai gov.cn Online]\n\n{{Hebei topics}}\n{{Hebei}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Xingtai]]\n[[Category:Cities in Hebei]]\n[[Category:Prefecture-level divisions of Hebei]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Xingtai County}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                 